"Electronic goods ticket" unique to return goods Setouchi city added with hometown tax: Sanyo Newspaper Digital | SanDigi
"E-City Gift."
it's settled by contacting a dedicated device.
Setouchi City announced on March 27 that it will add its own electronic goods ticket "e-gai gift" to the return goods of hometown tax.
It is available at member stores in the city from November.
It was the first municipality in the prefecture.
If you pay the hometown tax and choose an electronic goods ticket as a return item, 30% of the donation amount will be sent to the designated smartphone.
When purchasing a product, it shows the screen of the product ticket, and the shop side pays by contacting the stamp-type special equipment.
They cannot be sold or sold.
Recipients usually need a certain amount of time from application to arrival, but electronic goods tickets can be received instantly.
Tourists can use it easily.
In addition to the five Hometown Tax Portals, it is also accepted on two special sites in the city.
The company currently has 13 member stores, with a target of 100 by the end of this fiscal year.
In June, the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications (MIC) established a new system to regulate local products in order to prevent excessive competition among municipalities, after setting the amount of return gifts to less than 30% of donations.
The city has stated that it plans to make local products merchants affiliated with the city within the guidelines.
In fiscal 2018, Setouchi City's hometown tax was about 430 million yen.
