Driving in high heels is dangerous!
Accidents involving incorrect pedaling of young people - Yahoo!News
Violations in violation of the Road Traffic Act
The number of reports on accidents caused by incorrect operation such as pedal treading has been increasing, and it is a big mistake to think that this is a problem only for elderly drivers.
According to the 2015 National Police Agency data, more than 1080 pedal misstep accidents occurred at the age of 24 and over 1032.
It is important to call attention to young people as well.
do you want to take your feet off?
is it safe?
There is no description of gender ratio or cause in this data, but unlike elderly people who are often thought to come from a decline in their bodies, such as driving skills and reflexes, there is also a possibility that young people are inadvertently misled by other things such as music and conversation, and trampling errors due to clothes etc.
In particular, women choose various shoes depending on the clothes of the day and drive as they are.
Some people know that it is not suitable for driving, but it is troublesome to change shoes, but some people do not think about the possibility that it will lead to danger at all, and many people are driving without evil.
However, driving in high heels and sandals violates the Road Traffic Act.
The first is "Reliable operation of steering wheel, brake and other operations" and Article 70 "Disobedience of safety driving obligation" which stipulates that "Do not drive to cause accidents and harm to people."
The other is Article 71, which stipulates that drivers must comply with the matters stipulated by each prefectural public safety committee, for example, in Article 12 of the Miyazaki Prefectural Road Traffic Law Enforcement Regulations, "Do not drive a vehicle (excluding light vehicles) by wearing sandals, slippers, hanging, high heels or other footwear that may interfere with driving operation, or by wearing footwear in a manner that interferes with driving operation."
Even if it is not specified as a high heel, the purpose of each prefecture is the same as to regard driving as a violation of " footwear that may interfere with driving operation."
So why is driving in high heels dangerous?
It is obvious considering the basics of safely pedaling.
For safe pedal operation, first fix the heel of the foot on the floor, place the foot to be perpendicular to the brake pedal, and when stepping on the accelerator pedal, tilt the foot to the right as a supporting point.
At this time, regardless of the behavior of the car, it is important to secure firmly so that the heel does not break.
However, in high heels, the area where the heel is grounded on the floor is small, and the heel always blurs out, and because the height of the heel has an angle throughout the foot, the area of the foot that is grounded on the pedal is also smaller, and it is difficult to make fine adjustments that can not be stepped firmly.
This is considered dangerous.
In addition, most cars have floor carpets, but this material is easy to catch the heel heel heel heel heel and pedal can not be stepped in when suddenly braking, or high heel can be removed by the time the heel is pulled, and it can not be stepped in the back of the pedal.
In addition, there are cases where the heel is pulled to the back of the pedal when stepping back after stepping on the pedal, and the accelerator pedal is not returned.
Toyota and Subaru Accelerate joint development of new AWD vehicles and 86/BRZ next-generation models (response) - Yahoo!News
Toyota and Subaru agreed on a new business capital alliance on September 27.
Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares and become an affiliate of equity method application.
Since the partnership agreement was reached in 2005, both companies have been working together to produce Toyota vehicles, supply Toyota vehicles to Subaru, and jointly develop the FR sports car 86.
In June of this year, we agreed to work on developing EV-specific platforms and EV vehicles using Subaru's AWD technology and Toyota's electrification technology.
In this agreement, Toyota will acquire additional Subaru shares.
At present, Toyota's shareholding in Subaru is 16.83 percent of voting rights.
The company is a subsidiary of Toyota.
On the other hand, Subaru will acquire Toyota shares, which are equivalent to the same amount (up to 80 billion yen) as the acquisition of Subaru shares.
Both companies develop and strengthen cooperation through business capital alliance.
We will jointly develop AWD and 86/BRZ models, expand the installation of THS (Toyota Hybrid System) in Subaru vehicles, coordinate in the connected area, and promote technological collaboration in the autonomous driving field.
U.S., at least 18,000 refugees | Shizuoka Shimbun
Washington, D.C. On October 26, the U.S. Department of State announced a policy to reduce the number of refugees accepted from around the world to 18,000 in the fiscal year 2020 (October 19-20).
The minimum number of refugees since 1980 has been renewed for three consecutive years.
The Trump administration aims to appeal strict immigration and refugee policies to the conservatives in the presidential election next year.
It is inevitable that criticisms from human rights groups and other organizations come out in the midst of people being driven out of the country in various places.
The previous administration set the limit for fiscal 2017 to 110,000, but the Trump administration, which was inaugurated in January 2017, reversed this and reduced it to 50,000.
The number continued to decrease year by year to 45,000 in FY18 and 30,000 in FY19.
