The Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare (MHLW) confirmed by the 28th that there were similar cases in prefectures and government ordinance cities across Japan, and communicated in writing to provide guidance as needed.
According to the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare, several facilities were confirmed, such as raising the usage fee only for three-year-olds or older eligible for assistance, and raising the price in October.
There were also complaints about the free call center established by the Cabinet Office.
The Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare stated that "there is no reason to raise prices."
