Korea-Bulgarian Summit on Cooperation in Nuclear Power Plants and Defense Industries (Bulgaria) | Yahoo!
(SEOUL=Yonhap News) South Korean President Moon Jae-in met with Bulgaria's Prime Minister Borisov on his official visit to South Korea and discussed ways to expand bilateral cooperation.
This is the first time the Prime Minister of Bulgaria has visited Korea.
President Moon welcomed the visit to Korea before the 30th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations next year and highly appreciated the leadership of Prime Minister Borisov, who leads the development of Bulgaria.
The two leaders appreciated the continued increase in trade and investment between the two countries amid the expansion of protectionist tradeism globally and agreed to work together to expand economic cooperation in the future.
President Moon welcomed Bulgaria's policy of granting Korean companies a "strategic investor" position, and expressed his hope that this would facilitate Korean companies' investment in Bulgaria.
He also emphasized that Korea will be the best partner for Bulgaria as Bulgaria promotes the introduction of nuclear power plants and the modernization of defense, and called for attention and cooperation so that Korean companies can participate in the order of the Bulgarian government's nuclear power plants and the promotion of the defense industry.
In addition, the two leaders agreed to strengthen future-oriented cooperation in the areas of battery and auto parts for electric vehicles and renewable energy.
Prime Minister Borisov hoped to cooperate closely with Korea's leading ICT (information and communication technology) in the fields of science and technology and education.
He also talked about the Korean Peninsula's peace process, and President Moon expressed his gratitude for the support of the Korean government's efforts toward peace consolidation on the Korean Peninsula, such as Bulgaria's announcement of a statement supporting the North-South and North-America Summit.
Prime Minister Borisov appreciated President Moon's will to build a peace regime on the Korean Peninsula and the efforts of the Korean government, and reiterated the firm support of the Bulgarian government.
The meeting was attended by Jo Yunmo, Secretary of the Ministry of Trade, Industry and Energy, Lee Hao-houn, Chief Secretary of Economic Affairs of Chong Chong (President's Office), Kim Hyun-jong, Second Director of National Security Office.
The first official of the Department of Foreign Affairs, Zhao Se-yong, was also present on behalf of the Secretary of Foreign Affairs, Kang Kyung-fa.
Local industry in Hyogo and Awaji Island, Kinki Ceramics Co., Ltd., a manufacturer of Awaji tiles, filed for quasi-self-bankruptcy Liabilities of approximately 2 billion yen (Imperial Data Bank) - Yahoo!
It was also affected by the sluggish housing market and the progress of "consumer tile roofing away" due to frequent earthquake damage.
Kinki Ceramics Co., Ltd. (TDB Corporation Code: 530173983; capital of 9.92 million yen; 881-8 Otani, Awaji City, Hyogo Prefecture; representative Yukizo Fukuhara; 44 employees) filed for quasi-self bankruptcy at the Kobe District Court on August 30.
The applicant is Daichi Yoshida (1-10-8 Nishitenman, Kita Ward, Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture; Daichi Yoshida Law Office; telephone 06-6365-6038).
The company was founded in June 1895 and reorganized as a corporation in April 1961.
At first, he started his business as a manufacturer of ibushi tiles, a local industry in Awaji Island, in Nishitan-cho, Mihara County (present Minamiawaji City) under the trade name of Kinki Kiln Co., Ltd.
In October 1986, Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd. merged into Kyowa Kiln Co., Ltd., succeeded the business of Kinki Sangyo Co., Ltd., and at the same time, the head office was moved to the present location after changing the name of the present business.
After that, sales offices were established in Fukuyama City, Hiroshima City, Oita City, Miyazaki City, etc., and it became the current system, and Ibushi-gawara was mainly used before, but due to changes in consumer needs, Western-style tiles such as flat plate tiles were manufactured at 70% and Ibushi-gawara was manufactured at 30%.
The company has established a wide range of sales bases mainly in western Japan, including major house manufacturers, construction materials trading companies, and roof construction companies.
He was well known as the top tile maker in Awaji Island.
However, due to the sluggish housing market following the Lehman shock and the frequent damage caused by the Great East Japan Earthquake and the Kumamoto Earthquake, consumer demand was sluggish and annual sales for the fiscal year ended December 2018 were down to approximately 1.345 million yen.
On the profit side, in addition to a decline in the profit margin due to the surge in fuel prices, the company suffered a continuous deficit due to excessive interest-bearing debt associated with inventory burdens and business fixed investment, and was forced to make severe financial arrangements.
For this reason, although the Bank sought to rebuild its business by requesting financial institutions to ease the conditions for repayment of loans, there were no signs of recovery in business conditions and funding conditions were gradually tight.
I couldn't help but give up on business continuity and this is the measure.
The debt is currently under investigation, but is expected to be about 2 billion yen.
Prefectural Dinosaur Museum in Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture, which promotes the industrialization of tourism (photographed by Japanese aerial photography and a small drone drone)
Katsuyama City, Fukui Prefecture, announced on September 25 that it will acquire approximately 25,000 square meters of land adjacent to the construction site of the road station "Dinosaur Valley Katsuyama," which will open next spring.
In order to accelerate the "industrialization of tourism" advocated by the city and the local economy, we aim to attract accommodation-specific hotels and restaurants.
On the same day, a member of the Board of Directors of the Special Committee for the Promotion of the City Council explained.
With the opening of the Hokuriku Shinkansen in the spring of 2023, as well as the opening of the entire section of the Chubu Jukan Expressway within the prefecture, the expansion and renovation of the Prefectural Dinosaur Museum (Katsuyama City) and enhancement of functions, the city plans to move from day-trip center to stay-style sightseeing, and attract accommodation.
It is a private idle land located next to the east of the road station construction site.
Surrounded by the Kuzuryu River, Takinami River and the prefectural road, it is more than twice the size of a roadside station (about 12,000 square meters).
In the name of industrial complex development, the City Land Development Corporation will proceed with land negotiations from this fiscal year and build land in FY21 after acquiring land.
According to the city, there have already been inquiries from private businesses such as farmers' restaurants and harvest experience facilities, fast food, and restaurants.
As for accommodation facilities, it was also revealed that Sekisui House has promoted its name as a city to attract accommodation-specific hotels adjacent to Michi No Eki (roadside station) planned throughout Japan.
Sekisui House plans to expand into three locations within Fukui Prefecture, but it is said that there are other cities and towns willing to attract and may compete.
The city also plans to build a parking lot.
Some members called for speed-up when the maintenance schedule was slow, and others said that there was no place to sleep.
Mr. Mikio Mizukami, Deputy Mayor of the City of Katsuyama, expressed his intention to attract hotels and other facilities.
