BITPoint, which leaked 3 billion yen worth of crypto assets, to resume service (Genfusha Gold Online) - Yahoo!
In July of this year, 3 billion yen worth of crypto asset exchange such as Bitcoin leaked illegally.
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., which is the operator, announced on September 30 that it will resume the sending (remittance) service of crypto assets.
It seems that certain points were established, including measures to prevent recurrence.
BITPoint leaked Bitcoin and Ripple this July
Bitpoint Japan Co., Ltd., which operates the Crypto Asset Exchange BITPoint, announced on September 27 that it will resume the service for sending crypto assets (remittance) at around 14:00 on September 30.
In addition to dealing with customers who suffered damage and communicating with the Financial Services Agency, there seems to be a certain point of view including measures to prevent recurrence, such as management management system including security.
Bitpoint Japan says, "We will resume the service as soon as possible, while putting safety first, and strive to recover the trust of users."
In July of this year, there was an illegal outflow of crypto assets worth 3 billion yen, including Bitcoin and Ripple.
In the subsequent press conference, he mentioned that there is a current account balance of about 3 billion yen even if the amount of compensation is subtracted.
This article was released on September 27, 2019.
