Self-improvement of safety measures at Famispo 35% of municipalities implemented, free of charge for child care | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
Bereaved families of child-care accidents (right) holding a press conference on the results of the "Family Support Center Project" = Osaka Prefecture Agency
On March 27, a private survey revealed that 35% of municipalities in the city, wards, and villages that implement the Family Support Center Project (Famispo), which connects parents who want to temporarily leave their children and support members who are entrusted to them at their own homes, have independently strengthened safety measures.
Prior to the release of free child education and childcare in October, the family members of the child care accident complained that the government should make strict standards.
The "Network for Eliminating Serious Childcare Accidents" created by parents and experts who lost their children in an accident during childcare was surveyed by 921 municipalities.
274 municipalities responded.
The government's guidelines only require aid members to take emergency life training courses.
