[Saga Torrential Rains and Support Wheels] Specialty Noodles "Taromen" Serve at evacuation centers | Saga Shimbun News|Saga Shimbun
Children who enjoy the soul food "Taromen" in Omachi on their way home from the bath = Misato, Omachi Town General Welfare Center
"Omachi Taromen Steering Council" (Representative of Kensuke Suzuyama) made at a restaurant serving "Taromen," a specialty noodle of Omachi Town, performed "Taromen" at Misato, the town general welfare center, which is a shelter for the victims of heavy rain on the night of the 25th.
The soul food that was loved since the Kishima coal mine was there cheered the people affected.
"What we can do is make noodles and eat them."
Four restaurants on the taromen menu cooperated to make 90 meals and brought rice balls to shelter.
Udon noodles of thin noodles were added to ginger-flavored beef bone soup and plenty of ingredients such as pork head meat, shrimp, and vegetables were served.
Not only those who stayed at evacuation centers but also those who came to the baths provided "taste of Omachi."
A man (66) says, "I've been a fan since I was young, but I ate it for the first time in a year," and a 20-year-old and 22-year-old siblings who moved about a year ago and said, "I ate it for the first time, it's delicious, I want to go to the store this time."
Deputy Representative Kenichiro Fujise, who finished cooking, ran up and said, "I will cooperate if there is anything I can do so that I can return to my daily life as soon as possible."
1 year after the earthquake in eastern Iburi Province: Water supply even in the event of a power outage "Water sprinkling plug" will be installed directly connected to the water pipe Hakodate Mansion: Hokkaido Shimbun
In response to the total blackout (blackout) caused by the Iburi Eastern Earthquake in September last year, measures are being taken at condominiums in Hakodate City where water breaks out.
According to the Water and Sewer Department of the City Bureau of Enterprises, seven condominiums were installed in one year after the earthquake, and "watering plugs" were installed to allow water to be discharged even after power outages.
There are more than 400 condominiums and private housing units in the city that provide water with a "passenger tank type" that can be cut off during power outages.
The house's water supply system is broadly divided into two types: the "passenger tank type" that once feeds water into a receiving tank located underground or on the roof, and the "directly connected type" that directly feeds each door from the city's water distribution pipe.
Even if the water pipe is not damaged, an electric pump that scoops up water from the water tank to each door will not be able to run due to power failure, and each door will be cut off.
Training (Aomori Broadcasting Corporation) - Yahoo!
A training session was held in Shingo Village to search and rescue people who had suffered before the autumn mushroom harvest season.
A total of 60 people participated in the training held at Hirakozawa Forest Park in Shingo Village, including police, firefighters, and hunter-gatherers.
At the opening ceremony, Chief Tsukeda of the Goto Police Department called for close cooperation and training.
★ Takahashi Regional Manager's declaration "We will start mountain training rescue training from this."
The training was conducted on the assumption that a man who went out to see the mushrooms would not return home even at night.
The participants are divided into three groups and search the mountain by calling the name of the missing man.
In Shingo Village, a 70-year-old man who entered the mountain in June to pick up wild vegetables disappeared and was rescued with injuries the next day.
During the training, I found a man who had been injured and checked the cooperation from the search to rescue by putting him on a stretcher, and prepared for the autumn mushroom picking season which is prone to distress.
