Nike will release eight new models of Air Force 1 (AIR FORCE 1) that have been popular as sneakers representing the brand since its launch in 1982.
Three of the eight models are for women, and as Nike Women's Footwear Senior Creative Director Georgena James says, "Women are diverse and seek unique things that are different from others," an update has been added based on her experience in the collection "The One Reimagined" (released in 2018), which redesigns sneakers from a female perspective.
[Image] New 8 models of "Air Force 1" including NBA collaboration and models equipped with "Goretex" appeared at once
The Air Force 1 NBA Pack, in collaboration with the NBA, appeared in two types: low-cut and high-cut.
The low-cut is based on the NBA's red, yellow, black, and navy colors, while the high-cut is based on three teams, including the Los Angeles Lakers.
In addition to the NBA logo on the heel and shoetan, satin fabric is used behind the upper, and the swish is the first bicolor design.
The price was 13,200 yen including tax, and it was released on October 1.
"Air Force 1 Swish Pack" is designed everywhere with the letters and logos of Swish as it is.
It is noteworthy that the shoe tongue part, which should originally have a brand logo, has also been changed to the character of the special "SWOOSH."
The "Air Force 1 Shadow" is inspired by shadows and features double-sided details such as side washes.
The outsole is thicker and higher than the original, while hollowing out the center has succeeded in making it lighter for women.
The price was 13,200 yen including tax, and it was released on October 3.
