That's why YouTuber became a regular employee.
Ask the president who hired (bizSPA!
September 27 (Fri) 8:47
YouTuber is now very popular with young people.
Although it is not uncommon for companies to use it to advertise their products, some companies have started a unique system called "YouTuber adoption" that they employ as regular employees.
Direct Marketing Mix Co., Ltd. (DmMiX), whose main business is corporate CRM (customer relationship management).
What does it mean to adopt YouTuber?
We interviewed Dr. Yuki Kobayashi, Representative Director of DmMiX and Representative Director of Staff First, a subsidiary that actually adopted YouTuber.
I want to support young people who work hard with YouTuber.
What is YouTuber adoption in the first place?
Yuki Kobayashi (hereinafter "Kobayashi"): Now YouTuber is a profession that many young people admire.
It is also ranked in the top job rankings that elementary school students want to take in the future, and the number of young people aiming for will increase steadily in the future.
We have adopted and supported young people who pursue dreams such as bandmen and comedians.
In the same way, "YouTuber adoption" aims to support young people who are chasing their dream of becoming YouTuber.
Why did you decide to adopt YouTuber?
Kobayashi: While many young people yearn for the job of YouTuber, there is a reality that most YouTubers can't get the revenue they thought.
There are many creators who make and post videos while working part-time, and many creators who do not allow their family to recognize the existence of YouTuber.
In this initiative, we will provide an environment for salary and content creation to the creators we employ.
At first, we will support activities by supporting the disadvantage of the profession of YouTuber, which will inevitably become unstable.
