On September 26, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare announced for the first time the names of 424 public hospitals in 1455 national public hospitals and public hospitals such as JRCS, which judged that "the medical record is poor."
In Fukui Prefecture, the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare verified the treatment record of 14 public and public hospitals, and four facilities were targeted: Awa Hospital, the National Hospital Organization of the city, and Awa Hospital, and Sakai Municipal Three Kingdom Hospital, respectively.
⇒4 hospitals subject to reorganization: standards are wrong
In order to reduce medical expenses that are expanding due to the aging population, it was necessary to promote reorganization and integration with hospitals in competing areas.
In October, we will request a full-scale review of reorganization and integration at the target hospital, and we will conclude by September next year.
Although there is no compulsion force, local chiefs and residents are expected to rebel against the fear that nearby hospitals will disappear.
It was announced at the meeting on the same day.
The hospital covered 29.1% of the total, with relatively few beds.
By prefecture, Niigata (53.7%), Hokkaido (48.6%), Miyagi (47.5%), Yamaguchi (46.7%), and Okayama (43.3%).
The number of targets was 54 in Hokkaido, and Okinawa was the only zero.
Based on data from FY2017, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare investigated 1455 hospitals in public and public hospitals that can respond to "high acute phase" for severe patients and "acute phase" for general surgery.
He analyzed nine medical records, including cancer and emergency medicine, and whether competing hospitals were located within 20 minutes by car.
The hospital should consider abolishing and transferring some departments to other hospitals.
Medical expenses increased rapidly in 25 years, when all baby boomers were 75 years old or older.
For this reason, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare aims to reduce the number of beds in hospitals with 1,2466,000 beds (18 years) to 1191,000 beds nationwide.
Currently, there are many beds in the "altitude acute phase" and "acute phase" where nurses are placed thickly and medical expenses are required, while there is a shortage of rehabilitation for elderly people with high needs.
In order to cope with the aging population, it is necessary not only to reduce the number of beds but also to increase rehabilitation.
For the reorganization and integration of hospitals, each prefecture formulated a "regional medical concept" that defined the number of beds required for 25 years.
Although the country is divided into 339 districts, municipalities and medical officials are discussing it, many local residents and chiefs remain cautious and the debate is difficult.
The Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare wants to revitalize the discussion by publishing names of hospitals with poor results.
Comprehensive training on disaster prevention such as the assumption of Mt.Komagatake eruption, road, etc. Wide area with participation of residents, 18 years (video): Hokkaido Shimbun Ishin Electronic version
On September 27, a comprehensive disaster prevention drill was held in the forest, Nanae, and Kabe-cho in the Toshima-kan.
Approximately 400 people attended, including officials and residents of 20 institutions, including roads and three towns.
This was the first time since the Hokkaido Komagatake Volcano Disaster Prevention Council formulated an evacuation plan incorporating evacuation routes for residents in August.
It has been 18 years since local residents participated in extensive training.
At 8:45 a.m., Mt.Komagatake erupted and the mud flow reached the town at the foot of the mountain.
When the eruption alert level was raised to 5 (evacuation), evacuation shelters were opened in both Mori and Nanae towns, and residents moved by buses and police cars prepared by each town.
100,000 Students Appeal to Vancouver Climate Demo for School Break Global Warming - Yahoo!News
About 100,000 citizens, mainly students who sympathized with 16-year-old environmental activist Greta Tunberg, marched in Vancouver on September 27 to protest climate change.
Climate demonstrations in Vancouver
The march took place from Vancouver City Hall across Canby Bridge to the downtown library.
People with placards started gathering in front of the city hall of the meeting place a few hours before the start, and at 13 o'clock at the start time it was enough to fill the road of the city hall front block.
The number of participants continued to increase and eventually over 100,000 people participated.
On the road along the way, the police also cooperated with the road regulation and watched for hours until all people finished walking.
In conjunction with the United Nations Climate Action Summit held in New York, the city of Vancouver has held many events to think about global warming since last weekend.
On the 27th of the last day, a school strike was held on Friday for the future.
The students who took a break from school on this day appealed to adults, "I want to protect the earth even if I take a break from the school," and many adults who took a break from work responded, "We will do our best for the future of children who are seriously learning."
Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries (Gifu Shimbun Web) - Yahoo!
The Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries (MAFF) announced on March 27 that it would revise the quarantine guidelines to prevent the spread of pork cholera, a disease that has been transmitted to livestock.
The province will select nine prefectures, including Gifu Prefecture and Aichi Prefecture, where pigs and wild boars have been confirmed to be infected.
Vaccination of live pigs and fertilized eggs is restricted to the region, but distribution outside the meat and processed foods is permitted.
After public comments to the general public, etc., we aim to complete the procedure as early as October.
By using vaccines and allowing extraterritorial distribution such as meat, it is no longer a "clean country" certified by international organizations and may affect the export of pork.
Since the outbreak of September last year, Japan has been suspended for a while.
In the revised plan, the Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries set up a "Vaccination Recommended Area" based on the opinions of experts regarding areas with high risk of infection from wild boar to pigs.
The target prefecture will create a "vaccination program" that summarizes the scope, time, number of heads, how to proceed, etc.
Saitama, Toyama, Ishikawa, Fukui, Nagano, Mie, Shiga are the seven other prefectures that have been proposed as recommended areas for vaccination.
When the guidelines are revised, the region will review the situation and decide again.
The movement of inoculated pigs, semen, fertilized eggs, corpses, and excreted objects, etc., is limited in principle to the region.
As for meat and processed products, they are not targeted based on the cost of distribution restrictions and the impact on farmers, and they effectively tolerate distribution outside the region.
In order to prevent viruses from spreading, we will thoroughly process food waste.
He also advocates the safety of inoculated pigs and works to prevent harmful rumors.
The revised guidelines were compiled at an expert meeting held on the same day, and confirmed at a meeting of the Anti-Empire Prevention Headquarters.
In the future, we will conduct opinion inquiries and public comments to prefectures until October 7 and implement new quarantine guidelines.
