First Ice at Norikuradake Tatamidaira (Gifu Shimbun Web) - Yahoo!
Ice observed for the first time this season at Tsurugaike Pond in Mt. Norikura Tatamidaira = 27th morning, Tanseigawa-cho, Takayama City (provided by Norikura Skyline Management Office)
On the 27th, ice was observed for the first time this season at Tsurugaike Pond in Jodaira, Norikura-dake, Northern Alps (2702 meters above sea level, Nibugawa-cho, Takayama City, Gifu Prefecture).
Four days later than last year, one day earlier than the average of the past ten years.
According to Norikura Skyline Management Office, around 6:25 a.m., officials patrolling the road confirmed that about 2 mm thick ice was on the west side of Tsurugaike Pond.
The weather was fine and the temperature was 3 degrees.
According to the Gifu Regional Meteorological Observatory, the lowest temperature in the prefecture on that day was 9-5 degrees in Rokumaya, Sokawa-cho.
