Meeting with the Minister of Health, Labour and Welfare and Leprosy Families Three-State Consultations to Eliminate Discrimination | Shizuoka Shimbun at Es
Katsunobu Kato, Minister of Health, Labour and Welfare, announced at a press conference after the cabinet meeting on October 27 that he would meet with the families of former leprosy patients on October 2.
The Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare, Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology, and Ministry of Justice also announced on the same day that consultations will be held to resolve discrimination and prejudice against former patients and their families.
Mr. Kato said, "I want to listen carefully to the voices of the family members and make every effort to solve the problem."
In June, the Kumamoto District Court sentenced 541 plaintiffs to a total of 376 million yen.
Prime Minister Abe Shinzō postponed the appeal and the decision was finalized.
The government was also working on compensation measures and human rights awareness.
