Publication of the manuscript written before Akutagawa suicide | Shizuoka Shimbun at es
Original manuscript by Ryunosuke Akutagawa, which will be exhibited for the first time at the Tabata Bunshimura Memorial Hall
The author Ryunosuke AKUTAGAWA (1892-1927) obtained his own manuscript of his essay "Shokubun Bunshimura Memorial Hall" in Kita Ward, Tokyo by 27th, which he published in his last years, in which he fought literary theory with Junichiro TANIZAKI.
It will be exhibited at the museum from October 1.
Although it was known that his essay was included in the whole collection, it was the first time that his manuscript was published publicly.
It is thought that he wrote it a few months before Akutagawa committed suicide, and Jo Tanei, a researcher at the memorial hall, said, "I can see how Akutagawa, who was debilitating both physically and mentally, faced serious literary difficulties with a tragic resolution."
A total of 12 essays containing 200 characters were published in the April 27 issue of Bungei Shunju.
